channel.title: Two Quickly Made Models
channel.description:
Heres two models i made quickly, they just popped into my head..
Wine Bottle (Yes, they bottom is uneven, i couldnt be bothered to fix it, but im sure if its at weapon scale nobody will notice.) [img]http://i737.photobucket.com/albums/xx15/PiGReaR/Bottle.jpg[/img]
DL LINKZOR : [url=http://www.mediafire.com/?zeyeetokm4j]http://www.mediafire.com/?zeyeetokm4j[/url]
If one were to add this into their server, i would say they should add the drunk walk emote so when the wielded it, they walked like a drunk. xD
Bat [img]http://i737.photobucket.com/albums/xx15/PiGReaR/Bat.jpg?t=1258418534[/img]
DL LINKZOR : [url=http://www.mediafire.com/?zjcemdeytmn]http://www.mediafire.com/?zjcemdeytmn[/url]
Baseball Bat, for baseball perhaps? Or for bludgeoning someone to death?
BOTH OF THESE ARE MQO MODELS, NON-ANIMATED.

item.title: Two Quickly Made Models
item.dc:creator: @dylan_0789 dylan_0789
item.description:
@dylan_0789 wrote:

[quote=“Pigrear, post:22, topic:314532”][quote author=dylan_0789 link=topic=411009.msg3032930#msg3032930 date=1258509492]

Hah, his is way better.
I done mine when I was a beginner, and as I was practically the first modeller at moparscape, there were no tutorials or videos. :rolleyes:

haha same, i was modelling back when the rs datmaker was only theoretically created. before they even had a model section. i personally like learning through experimentation thn tutorials so i never followed tuts on modelling until i got into more complex blender functions =/

I think it was like, me first, then you started modelling here like, a week after, then ACF came when he saw some of my work.
Ahhhh, the good old days, when I didn’t even have 200 rep, I got it in less than a month. :P[br][br][size=1]Posted on: 18-11-2009, 00:08:41[/size][hr]Ah, I’m derailing the topic like fuck here, haha, back on topic, textures would be nice, even if the Metasequoia texture system is bollocks, also, you could lower the alpha setting on the bottle to produce a slight transparentness to the model.

it took forever for me to get 200 rep. since it was earned through model show offs, not releases.

and yea, on topic: why make such simple models? you insult yourself by doing such simple 5 min models. hell i could do those in 1 min each. try more complex things to better your skill faster
[/quote]

I have no fucking idea what to make. Lol. I do shit that pops into my head. haha.[/quote]
hmm, make a helmet from scratch. as in a plane, thats one of the things i find amusing to make (but i never post them).
